==Competitive record==
{{See also|Scotland national football team results}}

===FIFA World Cup===
{{Main|Scotland at the FIFA World Cup}}
Scotland did not compete in the first three World Cup competitions, held in [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]], [[1934 FIFA World Cup|1934]] and [[1938 FIFA World Cup|1938]]. [[FIFA]] ruled that all its member associations must provide "broken-time" payments to cover the expenses of players who participated in [[football at the 1928 Summer Olympics]]. In response to what they considered to be unacceptable interference, the football associations of Scotland, England, Ireland and Wales held a meeting at which they agreed to resign from FIFA.<ref>{{cite web|title=British Society of Sports History |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/development/technical/index/0,1250,7758,00.html?articleid=7758 |publisher=FIFA|date=19 August 1999 |access-date=31 May 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050904111234/http://fifa.com/en/development/technical/index/0%2C1250%2C7758%2C00.html?articleid=7758 |archive-date=4 September 2005 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The SFA did not rejoin FIFA as a permanent member until 1946<ref name="fifa member">{{cite web | title=Between the Wars | url=http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/scottish_football.cfm?curpageid=397 | publisher=Scottish Football Association | access-date=30 May 2007 | archive-date=16 March 2005 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050316233247/http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/scottish_football.cfm?curpageid=397 | url-status=live }}</ref> and also declined to participate in [[1950 FIFA World Cup|1950]] although they had qualified, as Scotland were not the [[British Home Championship|British champions]].<ref name = "withdrew">{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/50q.html |title=World Cup 1950 Qualifying |access-date=20 May 2010 |publisher=[[RSSSF]] |archive-date=20 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220720114854/https://www.rsssf.org/tables/50q.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

Scotland have since qualified for nine finals tournaments,<ref name="burley">{{cite news | title= Burley move pays off for Scotland | url= http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/soccer/world/events/1998/worldcup/news/1998/06/16/scotland_first/ | publisher= CNN | date= 28 September 1998 | access-date= 12 April 2007 | archive-date= 15 September 2000 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20000915081756/http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/soccer/world/events/1998/worldcup/news/1998/06/16/scotland_first/ | url-status= dead }}</ref> including five consecutive tournaments from [[1974 FIFA World Cup|1974]] to [[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990]]. Scotland have never advanced beyond the first round of the finals competition&nbsp;– no country has qualified for as many World Cup finals without progressing past the first round. They have missed out on progressing to the second round three times on goal difference: in [[1974 FIFA World Cup|1974]], when [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] edged them out;<ref name="brazil74">{{cite web | title=World Cup 1974 finals | url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/74full.html | publisher=Rec Sport Soccer Statistics Foundation | access-date=14 September 2008 | archive-date=11 December 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221211201424/https://www.rsssf.org/tables/74full.html | url-status=live }}</ref> in [[1978 FIFA World Cup|1978]], when the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] progressed;<ref name="cup78">{{cite web| title=World Cup 1978 finals| url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/78full.html| publisher=Rec Sport Soccer Statistics Foundation| access-date=14 September 2008| archive-date=7 December 2022| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221207104128/https://www.rsssf.org/tables/78full.html| url-status=live}}</ref> and in [[1982 FIFA World Cup|1982]], when the [[Soviet Union national football team|Soviet Union]] went through.<ref name="cup82">{{cite web | title=World Cup 1982 finals | url=https://www.rsssf.org/tables/82full.html | publisher=Rec Sport Soccer Statistics Foundation | access-date=14 September 2008 | archive-date=1 July 2016 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701154256/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/82full.html | url-status=live }}</ref>

