===UEFA Nations League===
When the [[UEFA Nations League]] was inaugurated in [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League|2018–19]], Scotland were allocated to [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League C|League C]]. With a 3–2 win against [[Israel national football team|Israel]] in their final match, Scotland won promotion to [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League B|League B]] of the [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League|2020–21]] competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46189774 |title=Scotland 3–2 Israel |first=Alasdair |last=Lamont |website=BBC Sport |publisher=BBC |date=20 November 2018 |access-date=21 November 2018 |archive-date=21 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181121000130/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46189774 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Scotland won promotion to [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|League A]] in their final match of the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League B|2022–23]] competition, a goalless draw against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] in [[Kraków]].<ref name = krakow>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62959155 |title=Ukraine 0-0 Scotland: Steve Clarke's side earn Nations League promotion |website=BBC Sport |date=27 September 2022 |accessdate=27 September 2022 |archive-date=27 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220927064111/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62959155 |url-status=live }}</ref> They were immediately relegated back to [[2026–27 UEFA Nations League|League B]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A|2024–25]] competition, after losing a playoff against [[Greece national football team|Greece]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c62zd1vpn3qt |title=Scotland 0&ndash;3 Greece |date=23 March 2025 |accessdate=24 March 2025 |website=BBC Sport |first=Amy |last=Canavan}}</ref>

